The maximum percent of stock which one person may hold in any association shall be:
Where the authorized stock is one hundred thousand dollars ($100,000) or less, an amount equal to four percent (4%) of the whole number of shares;
Where the authorized stock is over one hundred thousand dollars ($100,000), but not over five hundred thousand dollars ($500,000), an amount equal to three percent (3%);
Where the authorized stock is over five hundred thousand dollars ($500,000), but not over one million dollars ($1,000,000), an amount equal to two and one-half percent (2.5%); and
Where the authorized stock is over one million dollars ($1,000,000), an amount equal to two percent (2%).
Any association may restrict the number of shares which any person may own, to a percent less than that permitted by this subsection.
